BY 2.6 PERCENT.  THE STRONGER U.S. DOLLAR REDUCED SALES BY 3.3 PERCENT.  IN THE

UNITED STATES, SALES TOTALED $7.523 BILLION, DOWN 4 PERCENT FROM 2000.  U.S.

